@database F1GPAccessories

@node Main "F1GP Accessories disk - last updated 9 December 1995"
On this disk you'll find some useful utilities for use with MicroProse
Formula One Grand Prix (known as World Circuit in the USA).

Most of the programs need to be run from a Shell, rather than Workbench.
Installing them to a hard drive is usually just a matter of copying the
executable to where to want.  All the executables have also been crunched
so I can fit as much on the disk as possible.  All programs should work
on any Amiga (including ones with Workbench 1.x) unless otherwise stated
below.  Program list:

   @{"SplitTime 1.3" link "SplitTime/SplitTime.doc/main"}   by Renť Smit   (also PrintSplits)
   @{"AGPPerf 0.5h" link "AGPPerf/AGPPerf.doc/main"}    by Grant Reeve
   @{"GPDisplay 0.02" link "GPDisplay/GPDisplay.doc/main"}  by Grant Reeve (Workbench 2.0 or higher)
   @{"AGPLapTime 1.0" link "AGPLapTime/AGPLapTime.doc/main"}  by Renť Smit   (also AGPLap & @{"AGPLapMix" link "AGPLapTime/AGPLapMix.doc/main"} by Grant Reeve)

Note: the above programs aren't officially endorsed by MicroProse Software.

Also included is the latest edition of @{"Amiga F1GP Hall of Fame" link "HallOfFame.guide/main"} which is
maintained by Edo Nijmeijer, and some files / information on @{"F1GP-Ed" link "F1GP-Ed/F1GP-Ed.readme/main"}
which is distributed on a disk of its own.  There is also a replacement
installer for the game itself, which uses Commodore's Installer program
(which isn't on this disk due to lack of space).

Have fun...

